{"title_page": "Holly Williams (British writer)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2017}}\n{{Use British English|date=January 2017}}\n'''Holly Williams''' is a British arts and features writer and [[theatre critic]].<ref name=\"Hamlet\">{{cite news | url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/women/life/is-hamlet-sexist-meet-the-director-who-says-shakespeares-hero-wa/ | title=Is Hamlet sexist? Meet the director who says Shakespeare's hero was an abusive boyfriend | work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] | date=10 May 2016 | accessdate=2 August 2016 | author=Williams, Holly}}</ref><ref name=\"Thrones\">{{cite news | url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/tv/2016/06/02/why-game-of-thrones-is-bad-news-for-british-theatre/ | title=Why Game of Thrones is bad news for British theatre | work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] | date=2 June 2016 | accessdate=2 August 2016 | author=Williams, Holly}}</ref><ref name=\"Wanted\">{{cite news | url=http://exeuntmagazine.com/reviews/review-wanted-at-west-yorkshire-playhouse/ | title=Review: Wanted at West Yorkshire Playhouse | work=Exeunt | author=Williams, Holly|date=25 April 2016 | accessdate=16 September 2016}}</ref>  She grew up in [[Wales]], studied at the [[University of York]]<ref name=\"Journalism Matters \">{{cite web | url=https://www.york.ac.uk/english/news-events/events/2012/journalism-matters/ | title=Journalism Matters | publisher=[[University of York]] | work=English and Related Literature | date=2012 | accessdate=15 August 2016}}</ref> and worked for a local newspaper before moving to London. From 2010 to 2016 she worked at ''[[The Independent]]'' and ''[[The Independent on Sunday]]''.<ref name=\"Independent\">{{cite news | url=https://www.independent.co.uk/author/holly-williams# | title=Holly Williams | work=[[The Independent on Sunday]] | accessdate=2 August 2016}}</ref> Since 2016 she has been a staff writer for [[WhatsOnStage.com]].<ref name=\" Bowie-Sell\">{{cite news | url=http://www.whatsonstage.com/london-theatre/news/sarah-crompton-holly-williams-join-whatsonstage_40218.html | title=Sarah Crompton and Holly Williams join WhatsOnStage | publisher=[[WhatsOnStage.com]] | date=18 April 2016 | accessdate=2 August 2016 | author=Bowie-Sell, Daisy}}</ref> She has also contributed regularly to ''[[The Daily Telegraph]]''<ref name=\"Hamlet\"/><ref name=\"Thrones\"/> and the ''[[London Evening Standard]]''.<ref name=\"Standard\">{{cite news | url=https://www.standard.co.uk/author/holly-williams | title=Holly Williams | work=[[London Evening Standard]] | accessdate=2 August 2016}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.hollywrites.com/ Official website]\n*[http://www.whatsonstage.com/author/holly-williams_41/ Holly Williams on [[WhatsOnStage.com]]]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Williams, Holly}}\n[[Category:20th-century births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of York]]\n[[Category:British theatre critics]]\n[[Category:British women journalists]]\n[[Category:Daily Telegraph journalists]]\n[[Category:The Independent people]]\n[[Category:London Evening Standard people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2017}}\n{{Use British English|date=January 2017}}\n'''Holly Williams''' is a British arts and features writer and [[theatre critic]].<ref name=\"Hamlet\">{{cite news | url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/women/life/is-hamlet-sexist-meet-the-director-who-says-shakespeares-hero-wa/ | title=Is Hamlet sexist? Meet the director who says Shakespeare's hero was an abusive boyfriend | work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] | date=10 May 2016 | accessdate=2 August 2016 | author=Williams, Holly}}</ref><ref name=\"Thrones\">{{cite news | url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/tv/2016/06/02/why-game-of-thrones-is-bad-news-for-british-theatre/ | title=Why Game of Thrones is bad news for British theatre | work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] | date=2 June 2016 | accessdate=2 August 2016 | author=Williams, Holly}}<