{"title_page": "Indian locomotive class WDS-6", "text_new": "{{More footnotes|date=July 2019}}\n{{Infobox locomotive\n| name             = Indian locomotive class WDS-6 \n| powertype        = Diesel\n| image            = File:Indian locomotive class WDS-6.jpg\n| alt              = \n| caption          = Raipur WDS-6 doing some shunting jobs at Durg Junction\n| builder          = [[Diesel Locomotive Works|DLW]] , Central Railway Loco Workshop, Parel (Parel)\n| ordernumber      = \n| serialnumber     = \n| buildmodel       = \n| builddate        = 1975+\n| totalproduction  = 260+\n| rebuilder        = Parel Workshops\n| rebuilddate      = \n| numberrebuilt    = \n| Britishclass     = [[Co-Co locomotives|Co-Co]]\n| uicclass         = [[Co\u2032Co\u2032]]\n| gauge            = {{RailGauge|1676mm|lk=on}}\n| trucks           = \n| bogies           =ALCO Asymmetric cast frame trimount \n| wheeldiameter    = {{convert|1092|mm|ftin|0|abbr=on}}\n| trailingdiameter = \n| minimumcurve     = \n| wheelbase        = {{convert|12.834|m|ftin|abbr=on|frac=8}}\n| length           = {{convert|16.088|m|ftin|abbr=on|frac=8}}\n| width            = {{convert|2.864|m|ftin|abbr=on|frac=8}}\n| height           = {{convert|4.185|m|ftin|abbr=on|frac=8}}\n| axleload         = {{convert|21000|kg|abbr=on}}\n| weightondrivers  = \n| locoweight       = {{convert|113000|kg|abbr=on}}\n| fueltype         = [[Diesel fuel|Diesel]]\n| fuelcap          = {{convert|3000|L|abbr=on}}\n| lubecap          = {{convert|530|L|abbr=on}}, {{convert|630|L|abbr=on}} DLW\n| coolantcap       = \n| watercap         = {{convert|22|L|abbr=on}}, {{convert|28|L|abbr=on}} DLW\n| sandcap          = \n| consumption      = \n| watercons        = \n| primemover       = [[ALCO 251|ALCO 251-D]]\n| rpmrange         = 400-1100\n| enginetype       = [[Straight-six engine|Inline-6]] [[Diesel engine|diesel]]\n| aspiration       = [[Turbo-supercharger|Turbo-supercharged]]\n| displacement     = 267 mm\n| alternator       = \n| generator        = DC\n| tractionmotors   = 6 DC\n| cylindercount    = 6\n| cylindersize     = \n| transmission     =[[Diesel-electric transmission]] \n| multipleworking  =2 \n| maxspeed         = {{convert|71|km/h|0|abbr=on}}\n| poweroutput      = Max:{{convert|1400|HP|abbr=on}}<br>Site rated:{{convert|1300|HP|abbr=on}}\n| tractiveeffort   ={{convert|34.000|t|0|abbr=on}} maximum {{convert|16.050|t|0|abbr=on}} continuous\n| factorofadhesion = \n| trainheating     = \n| locobrakes       = 28LV-1, Air brake for Locomotive using SA-9 brake handle\n| locobrakeforce   = \n| trainbrakes      = Originally[[Vacuum brake|Vacuum]] , [[Railway air brake|Air]], some modified to [[Vacuum brake#Dual brakes|Dual]] \n| safety           = \n| operator         =[[Indian Railways]] \n| operatorclass    = \n| powerclass       = \n| numinclass       = \n| fleetnumbers     = \n| officialname     = \n| nicknames        = \n| axleloadclass    = \n| locale           =All over Indian Railways, Leased and sold to some industrial concerns\n| deliverydate     = \n| firstrundate     = \n| lastrundate      = \n| retiredate       = \n| withdrawndate    = \n| preservedunits   = \n| restoredate      = \n| scrapdate        = \n| currentowner     = Indian Railway, private industries\n| disposition      = active\n}}\n\nThe class '''WDS-6''' is a [[diesel-electric locomotive]] used by [[Indian Railways]] for shunting and doing departmental works. The model name stands for [[5 ft 6 in gauge railway|broad gauge]] (W), '''D'''iesel (D), '''S'''hunting  (S) engine. The WDS-6 is used all over India.\n\n==History==\nThe class was created in 1975 to address the need for powerful shunting locomotive that will be able to haul 20-24 coach rakes. The previous WDS-4 class was underpowered for this kind of operation. The WDS-6 locos consist of the [[YDM-4]] powerpack (6-cylinder 4-stroke inline Alco engine, turbo-supercharged) placed on [[Indian locomotive class WDM-2|WDM-2]] frames. They were manufactured by [[Diesel Locomotive Works|DLW varanasi]] and later Parel Workshops started building them using the kits provided by DLW.\nThe WDS-6 can easily be recognized by their shot nose and flat-ended cab at one end. They were sold and transferred to industrial concerns and public sectors in huge numbers, but have IR road numbers on them.\n\n== Some of the sheds holding WDS-6 locomotives ==\n{{columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n* [[Abu Road railway station|Abu Road]]\n* [[Bardhaman railway station|Bardhaman]]\n* [[Bokaro Steel City railway station|Bokaro Steel City]]\n* [[Diesel Loco Shed, Ernakulam|Ernakulam]]\n* [[Diesel Loco Shed, Erode|Erode]]\n* [[Gonda, Uttar Pradesh|Gonda]]\n* [[Diesel Loco Shed, Guntakal|Guntakal]]\n* [[Guwahati railway station|Guwahati]]\n* [[Howrah Junction railway station|Howrah]]\n* [[Itarsi Junction railway station|Itarsi]]\n* [[Jamalpur railway station|Jamalpur]]\n* [[Jhansi Junction railway station|Jhansi]]\n* [[Loco Shed, Kalyan|Kalyan]]\n* [[Katni railway station|Katni]]\n* [[Kazipet railway station|Kazipet]]\n* [[Krishnarajapuram railway station|Krishnarajapuram]]\n* [[Lucknow Charbagh railway station|Lucknow]]\n* [[Malda Town railway station|Malda Town]]\n* [[Moula-Ali|Moula Ali]]\n* [[Mughalsarai Junction railway station|Mughalsarai]]\n* [[Diesel Loco Shed, Golden Rock|Golden Rock]]\n* [[Diesel Loco Shed, Pune|Pune]]\n* [[Raipur Junction railway station|Raipur]]\n* [[Diesel Loco Shed, Ratlam|Ratlam]]\n* [[Diesel Loco Shed, Samastipur|Samastipur]]\n* [[Shakur Basti (Delhi Assembly constituency)|Shakurbasti]]\n* [[Tughlakabad railway station|Tughlakabad]]\n* [[Vatva (Vidhan Sabha constituency)|Vatva]]\n* [[Vijayawada Junction railway station|Vijayawada]]\n* [[Visakhapatnam railway station|Visakhapatnam]]\n}}\n\n== Technical specifications ==\n<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.irfca.org/faq/faq-loco2d.html|title=[IRFCA] Indian Railways FAQ: Locomotives -- Specific classes : AC Electric|website=www.irfca.org}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|Manufacturers\n|DLW, Parel Workshop\n|-\n|Engine\n|Alco 251-D, [[Straight-six engine|Inline-6]], {{convert|1,400|hp|abbr=on|lk=on}} ({{convert|1,300|hp|abbr=on|disp=or}} site rating) with Alco turbocharged engine. 1,100&nbsp;rpm max, 400&nbsp;rpm idle; {{convert|228|x|267|mm|in|2|abbr=on}} bore x stroke; compression ratio 12.5:1.\n|-\n|Transmission\n|Electric, DC-DC (DC Generator and DC Traction motor) \n|-\n|[[Traction motor]]s\n|GE for original Alco and MLW models, BHEL for DLW\n|-\n|-\n|[[Axle load]]\n|{{convert|21|t|abbr=on}}\n|-\n|total weight\n|{{convert|113|t|abbr=on}}\n|-\n|[[Bogie]]s\n|Alco design cast frame trimount ([[Co-Co engine|Co-Co]]) bogies \n|-\n|Starting TE\n|{{convert|34|t|abbr=on}}, at adhesion 27%\n|-\n|Length over [[buffer beam]]s\n|{{convert|17,370|mm|ftin|abbr=on|frac=8}}\n|-\n|Distance between [[bogie]]s\n|{{convert|10,516|mm|ftin|abbr=on|frac=8}}\n|}\n\n==See also==\n\n* [[History of rail transport in India]]\n* [[Locomotives of India]]\n* [[Rail transport in India]]\n* [[YDM-4|Indian locomotive class YDM-4]]\n\n===Bibliography===\n{{refbegin}}\n*{{Hughes-IndianLocos4}}\n{{refend}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n*https://rdso.indianrailways.gov.in/works/uploads/File/WDS6.PDF\n*https://www.irfca.org/faq/faq-loco2d.html\n*https://www.irfca.org/faq/faq-specs.html#WDS-6\n*https://www.irfca.org/apps/locos/list\n{{commons category|Indian locomotive class WDS6}}\n\n{{Broad gauge locomotives of India |state=open}}\n\n[[Category:Diesel-electric locomotives of India]]\n[[Category:Co-Co locomotives]]\n[[Category:DLW locomotives]]\n[[Category:Railway locomotives introduced in 1975]]\n[[Category:5 ft 6 in gauge locomotives]]\n", "text_old": "{{More footnotes|date=July 2019}}\n{{Infobox locomotive\n| name             = Indian locomotive class WDS-6 \n| powertype        = Diesel\n| image            = File:Indian locomotive class WDS-6.jpg\n| alt              = \n| caption          = Raipur WDS-6 doing some shunting jobs at Durg Junction\n| builder          = [[Diesel Locomotive 