ximum {{convert|16.050|t|0|abbr=on}} continuous\n| factorofadhesion = \n| trainheating     = \n| locobrakes       = 28LV-1, Air brake for Locomotive using SA-9 brake handle\n| locobrakeforce   = \n| trainbrakes      = Originally[[Vacuum brake|Vacuum]] , [[Railway air brake|Air]], some modified to [[Vacuum brake#Dual brakes|Dual]] \n| safety           = \n| operator         =[[Indian Railways]] \n| operatorclass    = \n| powerclass       = \n| numinclass       = \n| fleetnumbers     = \n| officialname     = \n| nicknames        = \n| axleloadclass    = \n| locale           =All over Indian Railways, Leased and sold to some industrial concerns\n| deliverydate     = \n| firstrundate     = \n| lastrundate      = \n| retiredate       = \n| withdrawndate    = \n| preservedunits   = \n| restoredate      = \n| scrapdate        = \n| currentowner     = Indian Railway, private industries\n| disposition      = active\n}}\n\nThe class '''WDS-6''' is a [[diesel-electric locomotive]] used by [[Indian Railways]] for shunting and doing departmental works. The model name stands for [[5 ft 6 in gauge railway|broad gauge]] (W), '''D'''iesel (D), '''S'''hunting  (S) engine. The WDS-6 is used all over India.\n\n==History==\nThe class was created in 1975 to address the need for powerful shunting locomotive that will be able to haul 20-24 coach rakes. The previous WDS-4 class was underpowered for this kind of operation. The WDS-6 locos consist of the [[YDM-4]] powerpack (6-cylinder 4-stroke inline Alco engine, turbo-supercharged) placed on [[Indian locomotive class WDM-2|WDM-2]] frames. They were manufactured by [[Diesel Locomotive Works|DLW varanasi]] and later Parel Workshops started building them using the kits provided by DLW.\nThe WDS-6 can easily be recognized by their shot nose and flat-ended cab at one end. They were sold and transferred to industrial concerns and public sectors in huge numbers, but have IR road numbers on them.\n\n== Some of the sheds holding WDS-6/AD locomotives ==\n{{columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n* [[Bardhaman railway station|Bardhaman]]- 2\n* [[Bokaro Steel City railway station|Bokaro Steel City]]- 11\n* [[Diesel Loco Shed, Ernakulam|Ernakulam]]- 1\n* [[Diesel Loco Shed, Erode|Erode]]- 6\n* [[Gonda, Uttar Pradesh|Gonda]]- 4\n* [[Diesel Loco Shed, Guntakal|Guntakal]]- 3 \n* [[Guwahati railway station|New Guwahati]]- 12\n* [[Howrah Junction railway station|Howrah]]- 18\n* [[Itarsi Junction railway station|Itarsi]]- 18\n* [[Jamalpur railway station|Jamalpur]]- 2\n* [[Jhansi Junction railway station|Jhansi]]- 11\n* [[Katni railway station|Katni]]- 3\n* [[Kazipet railway station|Kazipet]]- 1\n* [[Krishnarajapuram railway station|Krishnarajapuram]]- 3\n* [[Lucknow Charbagh railway station|Lucknow]]- 4\n* [[Mughalsarai Junction railway station|Mughalsarai]]- 13\n* [[Diesel Loco Shed, Golden Rock|Golden Rock]]- 1\n* [[Raipur Junction railway station|Raipur]]- 20\n* [[Diesel Loco Shed, Ratlam|Ratlam]]- 7\n* [[Shakur Basti (Delhi Assembly constituency)|Shakurbasti]]- 21\n* [[Tughlakabad railway station|Tughlakabad]]- 12\n* [[Vatva (Vidhan Sabha constituency)|Vatva]]- 17\n* [[Vijayawada Junction railway station|Vijayawada]]- 5\n* [[Visakhapatnam railway station|Visakhapatnam]]- 10\n*'''Loco Shed Izzatnagar-''' 1 \n*'''Loco Shed Unknown-''' 13 \n*'''Loco Shed Kharagpur-''' 17\n*'''Loco Shed Kurla-''' 51\n*'''Loco Shed Bondamunda-''' 8\n*'''Loco Shed Beliaghata Sealdah-''' 27\n*'''Loco Shed Andal-''' 6\n*'''Loco Shed Bandra Marshalling Yard-''' 24 \n*'''Loco Shed Gandhidham-''' 4\n*'''Loco Shed Patratu-''' 5\n*'''Loco Shed Ludhiana-''' 3\n*'''Loco Shed Tondiarpet-''' 12 <br />\n'''Total active Locomotives in service till March 2020:''' 378 \n}}\n'''Source-'''https://www.irfca.org/apps/locos/list?list_type=named\n\n== Technical specifications ==\n<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.irfca.org/faq/faq-loco2d.html|title=[IRFCA] Indian Railways FAQ: Locomotives -- Specific classes : AC Electric|website=www.irfca.org}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|Manufacturers\n|DLW, Parel Workshop\n|-\n|Engine\n|Alco 251-D, [[Straight-six engine|Inline-6]], {{convert|1,400|hp|abbr=on|lk=on}} ({{convert|1,300|hp|abbr=on|disp=or}} site rating) with Alco turbocharged engine. 1,100&nbsp;rpm max, 400&nbsp;rpm idle; {{convert|228|x|267|mm|in|2|abbr=on}} bore x stroke; compression ratio 12.5:1.\n|-\n|Transmission\n|Electric, DC-DC (DC Generator and DC Traction motor) \n|-\n|[[Traction motor]]s\n|GE for original Alco and MLW models, BHEL for DLW\n|-\n|-\n|[[Axle load]]\n|{{convert|21|t|abbr=on}}\n|-\n|total weight\n|{{convert|113|t|abbr=on}}\n|-\n|[[Bogie]]s\n|Alco design cast frame trimount ([[Co-Co engine|Co-Co]]) bogies \n|-\n|Starting TE\n|{{convert|34|t|abbr=on}}, at adhesion 27%\n|-\n|Length over [[buffer beam]]s\n|{{convert|17,370|mm|ftin|abbr=on|frac=8}}\n|-\n|Distance between [[bogie]]s\n|{{convert|10,516|mm|ftin|abbr=on|frac=8}}\n|}\n==Other Shunting Locomotives of Indian Railway==\n'''WDS-2:''' 30 produced - All are out of Service.<br />\n'''WDS-4:''' 662 produced - 11 are active in service.<br />\n'''WDS-5:''' 21 produced - 4 are active in service. <br />(April data is N/A so, don't change the data keep it as it is)\n<br />'''Source-''' https://www.irfca.org/apps/locos/list?list_type=named\n\n==See also==\n\n* [[History of rail transport in India]]\n* [[Locomotives of India]]\n* [[Rail transport in India]]\n* [[YDM-4|Indian locomotive class YDM-4]]\n\n===Bibliography===\n{{refbegin}}\n*{{Hughes-IndianLocos4}}\n{{refend}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n*https://rdso.indianrailways.gov.in/works/uploads/File/WDS6.PDF\n*https://www.irfca.org/faq/faq-loco2d.html\n*https://www.irfca.org/faq/faq-specs.html#WDS-6\n*https://www.irfca.org/apps/locos/list\n{{commons category|Indian locomotive class WDS6}}\n\n{{Broad gauge locomotives of India |state=open}}\n\n[[Category:Diesel-electric locomotives of India]]\n[[Category:Co-Co locomotives]]\n[[Category:DLW locomotives]]\n[[Category:Railway locomotives introduced in 1975]]\n