\n\nThe committee organizing the Durga Puja is headed by President Late Bal Chand Jaiswal and Chairman Lundeep Bhutoria.<ref name=\"Wala Unveils\" /> It has supported various charitable causes, including a donation of {{INR}}50,000 to disaster relief for victims of [[Cyclone Aila]] in 2009<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1090924/jsp/calcutta/story_11534774.jsp |title=Puja pick of right spirit |date=September 24, 2009 |newspaper=[[The Telegraph (India)|The Telegraph]]}}</ref> and {{INR}}100,000 towards the relief fund of [[Governor of West Bengal]] [[M. K. Narayanan]] in 2010.<ref name=\"Telegraph Potpourri\">{{cite news|url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1121019/jsp/entertainment/story_16106433.jsp#.VAN6PGNagmV |title=Potpourri |date=October 19, 2012 |newspaper=[[The Telegraph (India)|The Telegraph]]}}</ref>\n\nThe Manicktalla Chaltabagan Lohapatty Durga Puja has won the [[Asian Paints Sharad Shamman]] award for Best Puja in 1997 and for Best Artisan (Nepal Pal and Gouranga Pal) in 2002.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://asianpaints.com/25yearsAPSS/last_years.html|title= All winners list|work=[[Asian Paints]]|accessdate=2009-09-29| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20091003123908/http://asianpaints.com/25yearsAPSS/last_years.html| archivedate= 3 October 2009}}</ref> In 2010 it was introduced into the True Spirit Puja Hall of Fame.<ref name=\"Telegraph Potpourri\" />\n\n<gallery>\nFile:\u09ae\u09be\u09a8\u09bf\u0995\u09a4\u09b2\u09be \u099a\u09be\u09b2\u09a4\u09be\u09ac\u09be\u0997\u09be\u09a8 \u09a6\u09c2\u09b0\u09cd\u0997\u09be \u09aa\u09c2\u099c\u09be \u09e8\u09e6\u09e7\u09ec.jpg|2016\nFile:\u09ae\u09be\u09a8\u09bf\u0995\u09a4\u09b2\u09be \u099a\u09be\u09b2\u09a4\u09be\u09ac\u09be\u0997\u09be\u09a8 \u09a6\u09c2\u09b0\u09cd\u0997\u09be \u09aa\u09c2\u099c\u09be \u09e8\u09e6\u09e7\u09ed.jpg|2017\nFile:\u099a\u09be\u09b2\u09a4\u09be\u09ac\u09be\u0997\u09be\u09a8 \u09a6\u09c2\u09b0\u09cd\u0997\u09be \u09aa\u09c2\u099c\u09be \u09e8\u09e6\u09e7\u09ee.jpg|2018\nFile:\u099a\u09be\u09b2\u09a4\u09be\u09ac\u09be\u0997\u09be\u09a8 \u09a6\u09c2\u09b0\u09cd\u0997\u09be \u09aa\u09c1\u099c\u09cb \u09e8\u09e6\u09e7\u09ee \u09ae\u09a3\u09cd\u09a1\u09aa\u09b8\u099c\u09cd\u099c\u09be.jpg|2018\n</gallery>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://manicktallachaltabaganlohapattydurgapuja.com/Default.aspx Committee website]\n\n[[Category:Durga Puja]]\n[[Category:1943 establishments in India]]\n", "name_user": "Deb300193", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chaltabagan_Durga_Puja"}
{"title_page": "Catheline Ndamira", "text_new": "<!-- Please do not remove or change this AfD message until the discussion has been closed. -->\n{{Article for deletion/dated|page=Catheline Ndamira|timestamp=20200414131327|year=2020|month=April|day=14|substed=yes|help=off}}\n<!-- Once discussion is closed, please place on talk page: {{Old AfD multi|page=Catheline Ndamira|date=14 April 2020|result='''keep'''}} -->\n<!-- End of AfD message, feel free to edit beyond this point -->\n{{Orphan|date=April 2020}}\n\n'''Catheline Ndamira''' is a Ugandan Business woman and [[politician]] who has also been the [[Kabale District|Kabale district]] woman representative a position she held since  since 2016.\n\n== Background and education ==\nShe was born  on 13-Aug-1977.  Catheline Ndamira attended Rubirizi S.S.S. for her high school education. She studied Business at [[Makerere University Business School]], graduating with the Certificate in [[Business administration|Business Administration]] in 2008, She went on to obtain a [[Law practice|Diploma]] from [[Makerere University Business School]], in [[Kampala]] in 2010. In 2014, she obtained a Bachelor of Business Administration and Management from the [[Uganda Martyrs University]].\n\n== Work experience ==\n\n\nBetween 2010 and 2015 she worked as a financial Administrator at  VIDAS ENGINEERING SERVICES CO. LTD\n\nFollowing the [[2016 Ugandan general election|February 2016 general election]], Catheline was unanimously elected as [[Kabale District|Kabale district]] woman representative  on 2016.\n\n== Parliamentary duties ==\nBesides her duties as speaker of the Ugandan Parliament, she sits on the following [[parliamentary committees]]:\n\n* The Parliamentary Commission \u2013 She was a member \n* committee on health- Member\n\n\n`<nowiki>{{Poli-Stub}}</nowiki>  <nowiki>{{Stub}}</nowiki>\n<br />\n\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "<!-- Please do not remove or change this AfD message until the discussion has been closed. -->\n{{Article for deletion/dated|page=Catheline Ndamira|timestamp=20200414131327|year=2020|month=April|day=14|substed=yes|help=off}}\n<!-- Once discussion is closed, please place on talk page: {{Old AfD multi|page=Catheline Ndamira|date=14 April 2020|result='''keep'''}} -->\n<!-- End of AfD message, feel free to edit beyond this point -->\n'''Catheline Ndamira''' is a Ugandan Business woman and [[politician]] who has also been the [[Kabale District|Kabale district]] woman representative a position she held since  since 2016.  \n\n== Background and education ==\nShe was born  on 13-Aug-1977.  Catheline Ndamira attended Rubirizi S.S.S. for her high school education. She studied Business at [[Makerere University Business School]], graduating with the Certificate in [[Business administration|Business Administration]] in 2008, She went on to obtain a [[Law practice|Diploma]] from [[Makerere University Business School]], in [[Kampala]] in 2010. In 2014, she obtained a Bachelor of Business Administration and Management from the [[Uganda Martyrs University|Uganda Martyrs University.]] \n\n== Work experience ==\n\n\nBetween 2010 and 2015 she worked as a financial Administrator at  VIDAS ENGINEERING SERVICES CO. LTD\n\nFollowing the [[2016 Ugandan general election|February 2016 general election]], Catheline was unanimously elected as [[Kabale District|Kabale district]] woman representative  on 2016.\n\n== Parliamentary duties ==\nBesides her duties as speaker of the Ugandan Parliament, she sits on the following [[parliamentary committees]]:\n\n* The Parliamentary Commission \u2013 She was a member \n* committee on health- Member\n\n\n`<nowiki>{{Poli-Stub}}</nowiki>  <nowiki>{{Stub}}</nowiki>\n<br />\n\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "name_user": "CAPTAIN RAJU", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up, addedorphantag", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Catheline_Ndamira"}
{"title_page": "Brent Faiyaz", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{short description|American singer and record producer}}\n{{COI|date=October 2017}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name            = Brent Faiyaz\n| background      = solo_singer\n| image           = Brent portriat.jpg\n| caption         = Faiyaz in 2017\n| birth_name      = Christopher Brent Wood\n| birth_date      = {{Birth date and age|1995|09|19|mf=y}}<ref \nname=\"pigeonsandplanes-1\">{{cite web|url=http://pigeonsandplanes.com/interviews/2017/09/brent-faiyaz-interview-sonder-son |title=Everything Is Connected: An Interview with Brent Faiyaz of Sonder |date=September 21, 2017 |first=Adrienne |last=Black |work=[[Pigeons and Planes]] |accessdate=October 12, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"pulsemusic\">{{cite web|url=http://pulserecordings.com/clients/brent-faiyaz/ |title=Pulse Music Group Brent Faiyaz |publisher=Pulse Music Group |accessdate=October 12, 2017}}</ref>\n| birth_place     = [[Columbia, Maryland]], U.S.\n| alias           = \n| genre           = {{hlist|[[Rhythm and blues|R&B]]|[[Hip hop music|hip hop]]}}\n| occupation      = {{hlist|Singer|record producer}}\n| instrument      = Vocals\n| years_active    = 2014\u2013present\n| label           = Lost Kids\n| associated_acts = {{hlist|Sonder|[[GoldLink]]|[[ASAP Ferg]]|[[Juice Wrld]]}}\n| website         = {{URL|www.brentfaiyaz.com}}\n}}\n'''Christopher Brent Wood''' (born September 19, 1995), better known by his stage name '''Brent Faiyaz''', is an American singer and record producer.\n\n==Career==\n===2014\u20132016: Early career and ''A.M. Paradox''===\nFaiyaz began uploading his music onto [[SoundCloud]] in 2014 and moved from his hometown [[Columbia, Maryland|Columbia]], Maryland to [[Charlotte, North Carolina|Charlotte]], North Carolina before ultimately settling in Los Angeles, California to further his music career.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://artisticmanifesto.com/2016/09/19/brent-faiyaz-am-paradox/ |title=Stream Brent Faiyaz's fervid, soulful \u2018A.M. Paradox\u2019 debut |date=September 19, 2016 |work=Artistic Manifesto |accessdate=October 12, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171013013831/http://artisticmanifesto.com/2016/09/19/brent-faiyaz-am-paradox/ |archive-date=October 13, 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref> On January 19, 2015, he released his debut single \"Allure\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pigeonsandplanes.com/music/2015/01/premiere-brent-faiyaz-allure |title=Premiere: Brent Faiyaz \u2013 \"Allure\" |date=January 22, 2015 |first=Jon |last=Tanners |work=[[Pigeons and Planes]] |accessdate=October 12, 2017}}</ref> On June 1, 2016, Faiyaz released \"Invite Me\", the lead single from his upcoming debut EP.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hillydilly.com/2016/06/brent-faiyaz-invite-me-prod-by-pablo-dylan-james-harte/ |title=Brent Faiyaz \u2013 \"Invite Me\" (prod. by Pablo Dylan & James Harte) |date=June 1, 2016 |first=Tyler |last=Switsky |work=HillyDilly |accessdate=October 12, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://artisticmanifesto.com/2016/06/06/brent-faiyaz-invite-me/ |title=Brent Faiyaz embraces his vulnerability on 'Invite Me' |date=June 6, 2016 |work=Artistic Manifesto |accessdate=October 12, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171013014010/http://artisticmanifesto.com/2016/06/06/brent-faiyaz-invite-me/ |archive-date=October 13, 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref> On September 19, 2016, his 21st birthday, the EP entitled ''A.M. Paradox'' was released and received positive reviews from music critics.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pigeonsandplanes.com/music/2016/09/brent-faiyaz-am-paradox-ep |title=Brent Faiyaz Delivers Delicate Soul on \"A.M. Paradox\" |date=September 19, 2016 |first=Jon |last=Tanners |work=[[Pigeons and Planes]] |accessdate=October 12, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hillydilly.com/2016/09/brent-faiyaz-a-m-paradox/ |title=Brent Faiyaz \u2013 A.M. Paradox |date=September 19, 2016 |first=Nishant |last=Karvinkop |work=HillyDilly |accessdate=October 12, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://dailychiefers.com/brent-faiyaz-am-paradox-ep/ |title=Brent Faiyaz \u2013 AM Paradox [EP] |date=September 19, 2016 |work=Daily Chiefers |accessdate=October 12, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thisisrnb.com/2016/09/listen-emerging-artist-brent-faiyaz-releases-buzz-worthy-a-m-paradox-ep/ |title=Listen: Emerging Artist Brent Faiyaz Releases Buzz-Worthy 'A.M. Paradox' EP |date=September 20, 2016 |work=ThisIsRNB |accessdate=October 12, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://dayandadream.com/2016/09/22/brent-faiyaz-am-paradox-ep/ |title=Brent Faiyaz's Debut EP, \u2018A.M. Paradox,\u2019 is A Thing of R&Beauty [@brentfaiyaz] |date=September 22, 2016 |first=Bradford J. |last=Howard |work=Day & a Dream |accessdate=October 12, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://gurlgiltmusic.com/brent-faiyazs-a-m-paradox-a-nuanced-account-of-women-c5ce7e2fd8d1 |title=Brent Faiyaz's A.M. Paradox: Women as Muse |date=October 4, 2016 |work=Gurlgilt Music |accessdate=October 12, 2017 }}{{Dead link|date=October 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wherethemusicmeets.com/2016/10/18/brent-faiyaz-am-paradox-ep/ |title=Brent Faiyaz \u2013 AM Paradox (EP) |date=October 18, 2016 |first=Bea |last=Szwarc |work=Where the Music Meets |accessdate=October 12, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn October 2016, Faiyaz formed a group named Sonder with record producers Dpat and Atu,<ref name=\"pigeonsandplanes-1\" /> releasing their debut single \"Too Fast\" on October 25.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pigeonsandplanes.com/music/2016/10/sonder-too-fast |title=Brent Faiyaz, Atu, and Dpat Share Sultry New Single as Sonder |date=October 25, 2016 |first=Adrienne |last=Black |work=[[Pigeons and Planes]] |accessdate=October 12, 2017}}</ref> On December 16, 2016, Faiyaz was featured alongside rapper [[Shy Glizzy]] on the single \"[[Crew (song)|Crew]]\" by rapper [[GoldLink]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/rap-music/new-music/2016/12/goldlink-shy-glizzy-brent-faiyaz-crew/ |title=GoldLink, Shy Glizzy and Brent Faiyaz Start a \"Crew\" on New Single |date=December 16, 2016 |work=[[XXL (magazine)|XXL]] |accessdate=October 12, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===2017: ''Into'' and ''Sonder Son''===\nOn January 26, 2017, Sonder released their debut EP ''Into'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefader.com/2017/01/26/sonder-into-ep-premiere |title=Sonder's Sweet-Sounding into EP Is A Sincere Testament To Intimacy |date=January 26, 2017 |first=Lakin |last=Starling |work=[[The Fader]]|accessdate=October 12, 2017}}</ref> for which ''Duplion'' named them their \"Artist of the Month\" for January 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.duplion.com/sonder-into-ep/ |title=Sonder, Into EP (Brent Faiyaz, Atu, and Dpat): Artist of the Month |date=February 2, 2017 |work=Duplion |accessdate=October 12, 2017}}</ref> The EP was also ranked 23rd by ''[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]'' on its list of \"The Best Albums of 2017 (So Far)\" on June 6, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.complex.com/music/best-albums-2017/ |title=The Best Albums of 2017 (So Far) |date=June 6, 2017 |work=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]] |accessdate=October 12, 2017}}</ref> On June 21, 2017, Faiyaz was featured in the remix for GoldLink's \"Crew\", which also retained Shy Glizzy and included rapper [[Gucci Mane]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/news/2017/06/gucci-mane-goldlink-crew-remix/ |title=Gucci Mane Joins GoldLink for 'Crew (Remix)' |date=June 21, 2016 |first=Bryan |last=Hahn |work=[[XXL (magazine)|XXL]] |accessdate=October 12, 2017}}</ref> On March 8, 2019, Faiyaz featured on the song \"Demonz (Interlude)\" from [[Juice Wrld]]'s second studio album ''[[Death Race for Love]]''.\n\n==Discography==\n===Albums===\n====Studio albums====\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n|+ List of studio albums\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:13em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\